		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N York</placeName> <date>Septembr the 27. 1860</date></p>
				<p><addressee>The Rev. Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#8212;Permit me&#44; respectfully&#44; to recom&#45;<lb/>mend to your kindly notice that I have opened in <placeName>Cha&#45;<lb/>tham Street No. 94</placeName> a Bookstore under the Firm<lb/> <persName>Costez &#38; Guttmann</persName>.</p>
				<p>In consequence of an unexpected demand for Hebr.<lb/> prayer Mackizim<add>&#63;</add>&#44; chomasiem &#38; Tephiloth we<lb/> have by strong recommendations received<lb/> a depot of every kind from <persName>Frank &#38; Co.</persName> <persName>Ellinger &#38; Co.</persName><lb/> <persName>Rev. Dr. Bondy</persName> etc. in <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> we are glad to<lb/> be able to state that we have sold for the<lb/> Holy days a good <sic>assortiment</sic>.</p>
				<p>Now I request also your protection.  I live just in the best<lb/> part of <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> to sell Jewish books.  I self was in <placeName>Holland</placeName><lb/> &#40;whereof I am a native&#41; the Editor &#38; proprietor of<lb/> the Jewish Gazette and publisher of a great many<lb/> works.  I request also that you will take informa&#45;<lb/>tion for my person and business to <persName>Mrs. Frank</persName><lb/> <persName>Rev. Bondy</persName> <persName>Ellinger &#38; Co</persName> and to the <persName>Rev. Goldsmith</persName><lb/> <sic>wich</sic> Getln send to you his best respects.<lb/>  We wish to have in comm. in depot one or two of<lb/> your publications and you will do me a private<lb/> favor to inform yourself about our punctual<lb/> payments.  We will send you after selling directly</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>cash or any other way so as you are wishing.<lb/>  We will so we hope are able to sell with <add>&#63;</add><lb/><add>&#63;</add> of your Editions.</p>
				<p>What is the cheapest way to receive your good<lb/> from <placeName><sic>philadelphia</sic></placeName>&#63;</p>
				<p>The maybe that I will send from time to time<lb/> some articles for your Occident.  &#40;There is many<lb/> in the messenger of my hand&#41; will you correct<lb/> my English&#63;  I am not the best <sic>scolar</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">You will very much oblige with to take<lb/> information and to send your worthy answer<lb/> to your <sic>respectfll</sic> Servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Morr. Costez</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">of <persName>Costez &#38; Guttmann</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline">Booksellers</hi> <placeName>94 Chath. Street</placeName></p>
